reviews.review_text: Smokin' show This is a better copy of this show than the highly reviewed one. The sound quality is much better. And the boys were smoking this night

I love this show I'm not sure how I came across this show to begin with, but it was one of my first shows I burned on CD when I started to get into the Dead many years ago. To this day, this is still one of my favorite version of The Other One. The whole show is worth a listen.

MY FIRST SHOW I actually was at Woodstock but slept through the Dead's set. This was my first GD experience and being in the fifth row just added to the buzz.  All my friends at Columbia had hyped up the Dead beyond belief; luckily, they were up to the billing.  I was 10 feet from Pigpen, the coolest cat I have ever seen, and the higlight was the Dancin' in the Streets and Midnight Hour close. The energy and confidence that the band displayed in this era was fleeting, esp. given Pig's ultimate passing.  But hey now, Furthur's on fire and we're all dancing again.  This song ain't never gonna end!

a powerful night you can definitely hear some unique stuff here, as TC left the band a short time later. the boys gather the energy which would make 1970 such a huge year. some amazing jams, and the 'Black Peter' is one of my all-time faves as Jer just sings it out!
- Pretty good. The Other One especially is well-played.
